---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Start Here" description="What matterunknown is, why it exists, and where to go next.">
  <style>
    nav {
      position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; z-index: 200;
      height: var(--nav-h); display: flex; align-items: center;
      justify-content: space-between; padding: 0 var(--gutter);
      border-bottom: 1px solid transparent; transition: all .4s;
    }
    nav.scrolled { border-color: var(--amber-border); background: rgba(9,9,8,.93); backdrop-filter: blur(14px); }
    .nav-logo { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text); }
    .nav-logo span { color: var(--amber); }
    .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 32px; list-style: none; }
    .nav-links a { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .68rem; color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; transition: color .2s; }
    .nav-links a:hover, .nav-links a.active { color: var(--amber); }
    .nav-fund { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .62rem; color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: .08em; transition: color .2s; }
    .nav-fund:hover { color: var(--vessel); }

    .hero {
      min-height: 100vh; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: flex-end; padding: 0 var(--gutter) 80px;
      position: relative; overflow: hidden;
    }
    .hero-bg {
      position: absolute; inset: 0;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 60% at 20% 60%, rgba(196,151,42,.05) 0%, transparent 70%);
    }
    .hero-eyebrow {
      font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .64rem; color: var(--amber);
      letter-spacing: .18em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 28px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px;
      animation: rise .7s .2s both;
    }
    .hero-eyebrow::before { content: ''; width: 28px; height: 1px; background: var(--amber); }
    .hero h1 {
      font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(3rem, 6.5vw, 6rem);
      font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -.025em;
      max-width: 900px; animation: rise .9s .35s both;
    }
    .hero h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--amber); }
    .hero-sub {
      margin-top: 32px; max-width: 520px; font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.75;
      animation: rise .9s .5s both;
    }
    .hero-actions {
      margin-top: 48px; display: flex; align-items: center;
      gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap; animation: rise .9s .65s both;
    }
    .btn { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; padding: 12px 26px; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .72rem; letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase; transition: all .2s; }
    .btn-amber { background: var(--amber); color: #090908; }
    .btn-amber:hover { background: #d4a830; transform: translateY(-1px); }
    .btn-ghost { border: 1px solid var(--amber-border); color: var(--text-2); }
    .btn-ghost:hover { border-color: var(--amber); color: var(--amber); }

    .section-label {
      font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .64rem; color: var(--amber);
      letter-spacing: .16em; text-transform: uppercase;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; margin-bottom: 52px;
    }
    .section-label::before { content: ''; width: 28px; height: 1px; background: var(--amber); }
    .section-label::after  { content: ''; flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--amber-border); }

    .problem { padding: 100px var(--gutter); max-width: calc(var(--max) + var(--gutter)*2); margin: 0 auto; }
    .problem-inner { border-left: 1px solid var(--amber); padding-left: clamp(24px, 4vw, 56px); max-width: 720px; }
    .problem-inner p { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.5vw, 1.65rem); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: -.015em; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .problem-inner p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .problem-inner em { font-style: italic; color: var(--amber); }

    .pillars-section { padding: 0 var(--gutter) 100px; max-width: calc(var(--max) + var(--gutter)*2); margin: 0 auto; }
    .pillars { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: var(--amber-border); border: 1px solid var(--amber-border); }
    .pillar { background: var(--bg); padding: 48px 40px; transition: background .3s; }
    .pillar:hover { background: var(--bg-2); }
    .pillar-verb { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .6rem; color: var(--amber); letter-spacing: .16em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .pillar h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.45rem; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -.02em; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .pillar p { color: var(--text-2); font-size: .9rem; line-height: 1.75; }

    .audience-section { padding: 0 var(--gutter) 100px; max-width: calc(var(--max) + var(--gutter)*2); margin: 0 auto; }
    .audience-list { list-style: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--amber-border); }
    .audience-item { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 20px; padding: 22px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--amber-border); font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.6; transition: padding-left .25s, color .2s; }
    .audience-item:hover { padding-left: 8px; color: var(--text); }
    .audience-arrow { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .7rem; color: var(--amber); flex-shrink: 0; }

    .next-section { padding: 0 var(--gutter) 120px; max-width: calc(var(--max) + var(--gutter)*2); margin: 0 auto; }
    .next-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 2px; background: var(--amber-border); }
    .next-card { background: var(--bg-2); padding: 48px 40px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; transition: background .3s; display: block; }
    .next-card::before { content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 2px; background: var(--amber); transform: scaleX(0); transform-origin: left; transition: transform .4s; }
    .next-card:hover { background: var(--bg-3); }
    .next-card:hover::before { transform: scaleX(1); }
    .next-tag { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .6rem; color: var(--amber); letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .next-card h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.45rem; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: -.02em; margin-bottom: 14px; line-height: 1.2; }
    .next-card p { color: var(--text-2); font-size: .88rem; line-height: 1.75; }
    .next-foot { margin-top: 36px; display: flex; justify-content: flex-end; }
    .next-arrow { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--amber); transition: transform .2s; }
    .next-card:hover .next-arrow { transform: translate(4px, -4px); }
    .vessel-card::before { background: var(--vessel) !important; }
    .vessel-card .next-tag { color: var(--vessel); }
    .vessel-card .next-arrow { color: var(--vessel); }

    .footer-line { text-align: center; padding: 48px var(--gutter) 80px; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: .65rem; color: var(--text-3); letter-spacing: .08em; line-height: 2; border-top: 1px solid var(--amber-border); }

    @keyframes rise { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(18px); } to { opacity: 1; transform: none; } }
    @media (max-width: 768px) { .pillars, .next-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .nav-links { display: none; } }
  </style>

  <nav id="nav">
    <a class="nav-logo" href="/">matter<span>unknown</span></a>
    <ul class="nav-links">
      <li><a href="/start" class="active">Start Here</a></li>
      <li><a href="/mission">Mission</a></li>
      <li><a href="/vessel">Vessel</a></li>
      <li><a href="/projects">Projects</a></li>
      <li><a href="/writing">Writing</a></li>
      <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
    </ul>
    <a class="nav-fund" href="/fund">Fund the Research</a>
  </nav>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">Identity surface mapping</div>
    <h1>Identity is the largest<br>unmonitored <em>attack surface.</em><br>We map it.</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      matterunknown is an independent identity security research lab. We publish frameworks, build tools, and investigate the systems through which identity is exploited, manufactured, and erased.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="btn btn-amber" href="/writing">Read the research →</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/vessel">Talk to Vessel</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="problem">
    <div class="section-label">The problem</div>
    <div class="problem-inner">
      <p>Identity is not just a login. It is the thread running through every breach, every fraud, every coordinated attack on a person or organization.</p>
      <p>Most security programs monitor everything except the surface attackers exploit most. We call that surface. <em>We name it. We map it.</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pillars-section">
    <div class="section-label">What we do</div>
    <div class="pillars">
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-verb">Map</div>
        <h3>The full terrain</h3>
        <p>We track identity attack surfaces across technical, financial, narrative, and human dimensions — not just the credential layer. The threat is broader than most people think.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-verb">Research</div>
        <h3>Frameworks that don't exist yet</h3>
        <p>Deep reads on synthetic identity, biometric failure, the economics of impersonation, children and digital identity. We describe the problem first, then build toward solutions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-verb">Build</div>
        <h3>Tools that do the work</h3>
        <p>Vessel, the council architecture, the quant model, identity surface experiments. Open where it should be, contained where it must be. Everything documented in public.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="audience-section">
    <div class="section-label">Who this is for</div>
    <ul class="audience-list">
      <li class="audience-item"><span class="audience-arrow">→</span>Security practitioners tired of vendor noise who want actual frameworks</li>
      <li class="audience-item"><span class="audience-arrow">→</span>Founders and operators who know identity matters but don't know where to look</li>
      <li class="audience-item"><span class="audience-arrow">→</span>Researchers and writers mapping the edges of this problem</li>
      <li class="audience-item"><span class="audience-arrow">→</span>Anyone who has ever had their identity used against them</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="next-section">
    <div class="section-label">Where to go next</div>
    <div class="next-grid">
      <a class="next-card" href="/writing">
        <div class="next-tag">Research</div>
        <h3>The deep work</h3>
        <p>Frameworks, essays, long reads. Identity and death. Synthetic fraud. Biometric failure. The NHI problem. Break glass access.</p>
        <div class="next-foot"><span class="next-arrow">↗</span></div>
      </a>
      <a class="next-card vessel-card" href="/vessel">
        <div class="next-tag">Vessel</div>
        <h3>Ask it anything</h3>
        <p>Vessel is an AI research collaborator that knows the work. Ask about identity security — it's built to think alongside you, not just retrieve answers.</p>
        <div class="next-foot"><span class="next-arrow">↗</span></div>
      </a>
      <a class="next-card" href="/fund">
        <div class="next-tag">Fund</div>
        <h3>Keep it alive</h3>
        <p>No investors. No advertisers. No agenda except the work. If this is useful, the best thing you can do is support it directly.</p>
        <div class="next-foot"><span class="next-arrow">↗</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="footer-line">
    matterunknown is an independent research lab.<br>
    No investors. No advertisers. No agenda except the work.
  </div>

  <script>
    const nav = document.getElementById('nav');
    window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
      nav.classList.toggle('scrolled', scrollY > 16);
    }, { passive: true });
  </script>
</Base>
